  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi @aymeric-giraudet \r\n\r\nThanks for taking the time to help 🙂  \r\n\r\nI have created this sandbox:\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/nice-phoebe-c5qxtt\r\n\r\nI have the same issue with the page router in Nextjs as well as the app router. I am unsure how to sync the query variables with the URL(and still be able to navigate back and forth in the history of the Nextjs router). I want a search modal on top of the page making it possible to search all app/page content.\r\n\r\nI am looking at this page:\r\nhttps://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/instantsearch-next-router/react/\r\nHere it is explicitly stated that:\r\n`createInstantSearchNextRouter() is a function that creates a Next.js-compatible InstantSearch router to pass to InstantSearch... ...This function cannot be used in conjunction with getStaticProps. Use getServerSideProps() or client-side rendering instead.`\r\n\r\nI have tried making a very basic codesandbox - but all the Algolia code will of course be lazy-loaded when the user opens the modal the first time. \r\n\r\nThis functionality seemed fairly easy to do with React InstantSearch v6. But in v7 in the Nextjs app router I have a hard time figuring out how to do this.\r\n",
